Name: 5CWQ.A
Comments: Flat toroid	 because the elevation is not sufficient to continue the SH without a clash. Up to 6 two-helical repeats are possible	 so it is an incomplete C6 with 4 repeats. On the other hand	 each helix has consistent orientation	 so if the elevation were sufficient a SH6H2 symmetry could be formed.
